gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Rockets 127, Bulls 117
gameRecap.excerpt: The Rockets won their seventh game in a row as they defeated the Bulls, 127-117. Jalen Green led Houston with 26 points, four rebounds, and three assists as Dillon Brooks added 23 points. Amen Thompson totaled 15 points and eight rebounds as he continues to surge since the injury to Alperen Sengun. Ayo Donsunmu led the Bulls with a career-high 35 points while Nikola Vucevic added 16 points, 14 rebounds, and six assists. Houston improves to 34-35 as the Bulls move to 34-36.
